2026-06-12
- Softened native ISP agent replies so package, price, and early installation questions no longer ask for customer identity too early.
- Adjusted package/price overview ranking so broad "paket dan harga" questions enter the package information flow.
- Delayed name and phone collection until an explicit processing/confirmation stage while still allowing memory to capture those slots if provided.
- Added tests for soft package, price, and installation follow-up behavior.

2026-06-11
- Added SQLite-backed native conversation memory through `conversation_states` so the ISP agent can continue slot collection across webhook messages.
- Updated the CS/Sales agent to fill pending slots from follow-up messages before reclassifying them as new intents.
- Added memory-aware replies for collected address, area, usage need, customer name, and phone number details.
- Documented the native LLM memory architecture, OpenAI helper boundaries, and Redis deferral guidance.
- Added unit tests for memory-based follow-up slot filling.
- Added OpenAI Learning Queue suggestion support with `OPENAI_API_KEY`, default `OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini`, a protected suggestion endpoint, and dashboard autofill.

2026-06-09
- Removed tracked root SQL/schema seed artifacts from the repository and moved default intent/entity seed data into an internal backend Python module.
- Added a learning queue for low-confidence or unknown chat messages so unprocessed customer questions can be reviewed before future OpenAI API fallback.
- Added SQLite persistence for `unprocessed_questions` with mapping status, candidates, entities, and reviewer metadata.
- Added protected learning endpoints to list review items, list intents, and map questions into `sample_utterances` and/or `keywords`.
- Added a Learning Queue tab to the dashboard for mapping unresolved customer questions without using raw SQL.
- Improved ISP CS/Sales agent question matching by combining weighted keyword ranking, sample utterance similarity, token suffix expansion, and ISP-specific heuristic boosts.
- Added sample utterances to the SQLite agent catalog so seeded customer questions can improve intent classification.
- Added reply templates for detected but previously unmapped intents to reduce fallback "Maaf Kak" responses.
- Added Indonesian slang normalization for common customer phrases such as `brp`, `berapaan`, `udah`, `gak`, and coverage synonyms.
- Added unit tests for precise price, coverage, Sundanese package, and technician follow-up matching.

2026-06-08
- Migrated stock lookup from Google Sheets to SQLite by adding the `stock_products` table scoped per client.
- Removed runtime Google Sheets logging/lookup from the chatbot flow; inbound and outbound chat data now stays in SQLite messages/conversations.
- Added API endpoints to list and upsert stock products through `/api/v1/chat/stock-products`.
- Removed Google Sheets environment variables and Google API dependencies from backend dependency files.
- Updated backend documentation to describe the SQLite-only stock workflow.
- Added SQLite intent/entity reference tables from `DB.md` and idempotent seed loading from root SQL/JSON files.
- Added `python -m app.cli.init_sqlite` to initialize and seed SQLite without starting the web server.
- Added a SQLite-backed ISP CS/Sales agent that classifies intent, extracts entities, detects missing slots, and composes customer replies.
- Added `/api/v1/chat/agent/preview` to test agent replies without sending WhatsApp messages.
- Added validation to skip chatbot replies when incoming webhook payloads have empty or null `message_text`.

2026-06-06
- Restructured the project so the repository root contains `backend/` and `frontend/`.
- Moved the SQLite explorer frontend back to the top-level `frontend/` folder.
- Updated backend runtime paths, docs, and Railway watch patterns to match the new layout.
- Moved the example environment file to the repository root and updated dotenv loading to read from root `.env`.
- Fixed the local reload helper so it enters `backend/` before launching uvicorn from the root project.
- Added a legacy Railway config shim at `apps/backend/railway.toml` so deployments still pointing at the old service config path can initialize successfully while the canonical config remains in `backend/railway.toml`.
- Added root-level Railway bridge files (`requirements.txt` and `start.sh`) so Railpack can detect Python from the repository root and start the backend through the new root layout.
- Updated Railway start commands to call `bash start.sh` instead of depending on a backend-local entrypoint.
- Expanded Railway watch patterns to include the root deployment bridge files so changes to `requirements.txt` and `start.sh` trigger rebuilds too.
- Added a root-level `railway.toml` and updated deploy docs so Railway can target the repository root cleanly with the new layout.
- Changed root `requirements.txt` to list backend dependencies directly because Railpack installs it before nested project files such as `backend/requirements.txt` are available in the build layer.
- Made SQLite explorer source parsing accept a single JSON object as well as an array, and documented Railway SQLite paths using `/app/data/chat.sqlite3`.
